<br>
I'm going to generalize encounters into 2 types: defensive warrior, and other.<br>
<br>
Basically for most end game mobs, you need a defensive warrior for the simple efficiency of complete heal on a huge pool of hps, plus the reduction in damage recieved.  For other encounters, for example, lower difficulty epic fights, you'll be fine using a paladin, sk, whatever to tank.  In some cases, more rare, the high avoidance ac of a monk may be useful compared to mitigation, perhaps on proccing mobs?  This is something I'm not entirely sure of.<br>
<br>
As for what an MA should know, hmmm.... you have to know how long you need to build aggro before sending your force onto the mob, and how to hold aggro on yourself as well as possible.  Same for SA, with the added complication of having to jump to the top of the hate list mid fight, when no one is near as likely to back down.<br>
<br>
*shrug* I'm not going to say much more than that w/o personal experience. <p>-----------------------------<BR><A HREF='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112438' target=new>Rhatha Sha`Naya</A> and Swiftclaw <Ebon Storm><BR>
